title: Palo Alto: DoS Zone RED Drops
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/network/palo_alto
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the packet drops of the DoS protection zone RED
 action of a Palo Alto firewall. It reads the two counters
 panFlowDosZoneRedAct (.1.3.6.1.4.1.25461.2.1.2.1.19.8.31, "Activate")
 and panFlowDosZoneRedMax (.1.3.6.1.4.1.25461.2.1.2.1.19.8.32, "Maximum")
 from the PAN-COMMON-MIB and reports both as packets per second.

 Both drop rates are shown together in one combined graph. Optional upper
 levels for each rate can be configured via the rule "Palo Alto DoS Zone
 RED Drops"; by default no levels are applied.

discovery:
 One service is created if the firewall exposes the DoS zone RED counters.
